{
  "_comment": [
    "Batch-2 aggressive lexicon expansion: high-frequency Turkish NOUNs (institutional,",
    "politics/economy, society/culture, nature, health, education, daily-life, abstract).",
    "No engine change — all inflect through the existing nominal FSM.",
    "",
    "VOICING POLICY (opt-in engine => omission is always safe): attributes=['voicing'] is set",
    "ONLY where the final stop VERIFIABLY softens before a vowel suffix:",
    "  - polysyllabic -lIk/-lUk abstracts (sorumluluk->sorumluluğu, yönetmelik->yönetmeliği);",
    "  - other polysyllabic native -k (dernek->derneği, emek->emeği, destek->desteği);",
    "  - polysyllabic ç (süreç->süreci, inanç->inancı, utanç->utancı);",
    "  - individually-verified Arabic p (talep->talebi).",
    "NOT flagged (kept a plain stop before a vowel, per TDK): t-final loans (hükümet->hükümeti,",
    "cumhuriyet, siyaset, ticaret, şart, semt, boyut, hizmet — devlet-class); f-final (taraf,",
    "teklif, tarif, esnaf); v-final (görev/ödev/grev). A wrong voicing flag silently licenses a",
    "false analysis (*hükümedi), so unverified stop-finals are omitted rather than guessed.",
    "",
    "DEFERRED (NOT added — documented per the correctness-over-coverage contract): 3sg-possessive-",
    "FUSED compounds (gökyüzü, ayakkabı, havaalanı). The engine has no compound attribute, so a",
    "plain entry would generate *gökyüzüde instead of the pronominal-n gökyüzünde — a WRONG",
    "paradigm. Left to the guesser / a future compound milestone."
  ],
